<F P=100> Economic &amp; Agricultural </F>
<H3> <TI>   Northeast Region Promotes Grain Production </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Northeast Region Promotes Grain Production </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1106051794 Beijing XINHUA in English 0327 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1106051794 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Shenyang, June 11 (XINHUA) -- Northeast China has 
taken a series of steps to increase grain output this year. 
  Latest figures show that the seeded area this spring in 
Liaoning, Jilin and Heilongjiang provinces increased by nearly 
one million hectares, including 400,000 hectares of beans and 
wheat, and more high-yielding crops such as corn and rice were 
sown. 
  This will increase the grain output in the region by an 
estimated 7.2 billion kg this year, said a local grain 
production planning official. 
  By mid-may, Heilongjiang Province had injected more than 
5.73 
billion yuan to boost its agricultural production. The major 
part of the funds -- 65.3 percent -- was raised by the farmers. 
  In Liaoning and Jilin, more money has been used to buy 
fertilizers. In addition, over 250 million cu m of manure has 
been applied in Liaoning and Heilongjiang. 
  Northeast China's total of cultivated land is 16 million 
hectares, and its rural population numbers 57 million. It is 
one of the country's biggest grain producers, with advanced 
mechanized farm machinery. 
  The region's overall grain output last year reached a record 
60 billion kg, accounting for 13 percent of the country's total. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

