<H3> <TI>   Large Steel Furnace Starts Operation in Anhui </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Large Steel Furnace Starts Operation in Anhui </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1006132494 Beijing XINHUA in English 1312 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1006132494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hefei, June 10 (XINHUA) -- A furnace with a volume 
of 2,500 cubic meters went into operation in Maanshan Thursday 
[9 June], a major iron and steel production center in east 
China's Anhui Province. 
  The furnace is designed to produce 1.75 million tons of pig 
iron annually. It was built by the Maanshan Iron and Steel 
Company at a total cost of 3.23 billion yuan. 
  Chinese Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua attended a ceremony to mark 
the operation of the furnace, a top-priority construction 
project in China. 

</TEXT>

