<F P=100> PRC MEDIA ON TAIWAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Trio Confess During Trial </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Trio Confess During Trial </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1006205294 Beijing XINHUA in English 1640 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1006205294 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hangzhou, June 10 (XINHUA) -- The three men accused 
of the murder of 32 people in the March 31 Qiandao Lake tragedy 
confessed their guilt in a court investigation conducted here 
today. 
  The trial of the three accused Wu Lihong, Hu Zhihan and Yu 
Aijun opened here today in public in the Intermediate People's 
Court of Hangzhou city in east China's Zhejiang Province. 
  In the court investigation, the three accused all confessed 
that they committed the robbery and intentional homicide crime 
that they are accused of in the indictment. 
  At the court, judges interrogated the accused in detail and 
witnesses gave evidence. 
  The court argument will be conducted tomorrow according to 
the trial procedure. 
  The intermediate court also announced this afternoon that 
the 
trial of Wu Liming, who is accused of harboring robbed goods, 
will open in public on June 13. 

</TEXT>

