<H3> <TI>   Court Sentences Accused to Death </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Court Sentences Accused to Death </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1206070194 Beijing XINHUA in English 0648 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1206070194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hangzhou, June 12 (XINHUA) -- The three murderers 
who killed 32 people, mainly tourists from Taiwan in the March 
31 Qiandao Lake tragedy, were sentenced to death and deprived of 
political rights for life here today. 
  The judgment was pronounced today by the intermediate 
people's court of Hangzhou city in east China's Zhejiang 
Province. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-25625 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi113_u_94004" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-CHI-94-113 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  12 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> PRC MEDIA ON TAIWAN AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Further on Death Sentences </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Further on Death Sentences </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1206094494 Beijing XINHUA in English 0919 GMT 12 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1206094494 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Hangzhou, June 12 (XINHUA) -- Three men accused of 
robbery and murder in the March 31 Qiandao Lake tragedy were 
sentenced to death and deprived of political rights for life 
here today. 
  The judgment of first instance was made earlier today by the 
intermediate people's court of Hangzhou city in east China's 
Zhejiang Province. 
  The court ruled that the facts of the crimes were clear and 
the evidence was complete. 
  The court verdict, read out by Yang Gang, president of the 
intermediate people's court of Hangzhou city, said that Wu 
Lihong, Hu Zhihan and Yu Aijun had committed robbery and murder 
in the boat-fire tragedy, which claimed the lives of 24 Taiwan 
tourists and eight mainland crew, at Qiandao Lake, a major 
tourist attraction in Zhejiang Province. 
  It said that the three men seized large quantities of the 
tourists' property by threatening them with violence and then 
murdered the victims by blowing up the boat and setting fire to 
it to cover up the crime, and the punishment was for both 
robbery and murder. 
  The court turned down the defence lawyers' appeal for 
lenient 
punishment, because the crimes were very serious, cruel and 
caused great harm to the society. 
  The court also ordered that the robbed goods and money be 
returned to relatives of the victims, and the motor boat used by 
the criminals be confiscated and turned over to the state. 
  According to law, the three accused can appeal, either 
through the intermediate court of Hangzhou city or directly, to 
the higher people's court of Zhejiang Province within three days 
after they received the verdicts, which had already been handed 
to them today. 
  More than 200 people were present to hear the judgment at 
the 
court today, including local residents, relatives of victims 
from the mainland, and representatives of the Soaring Travel 
Service of Taiwan. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-25626 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drchi113_u_94005" </HT>


