<F P=100> Northeast Asia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Japan Foreign Minister To Visit South Korea, China </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japan Foreign Minister To Visit South Korea, China </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1006145994 Beijing XINHUA in English 1440 GMT 10 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1006145994 </F>
<F P=104>  Beijing XINHUA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 10 (XINHUA) -- Japanese Foreign Minister 
Koji Kakizawa will visit South Korea and China Saturday [11 
June] and Sunday for talks with his counterparts on the nuclear 
issue in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK), the 
Foreign Ministry said today. 
  During his stay in Seoul tomorrow, Kakizawa will meet South 
Korean Foreign Minister Han Sung-chu to have a wide-ranging 
exchange of views on such issues as the international situation 
including the nuclear problem, the ministry said. 
  The Japanese foreign minister will also pay a courtesy call 
on President Kim Yong-sam. 
  While in Beijing on Sunday, Kakizawa is scheduled to meet 
Chinese Vice Premier and Foreign Minister Qian Qichen to have 
talks mainly on the nuclear issue, the ministry said. 

</TEXT>

