<F P=100> NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political &amp; Social </F>
<H3> <TI>   Spokesman Refutes Foreign Ministry Reshuffle Rumors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Spokesman Refutes Foreign Ministry Reshuffle Rumors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   HK1206052194 Hong Kong HONG KONG STANDARD in English 11 Jun 
94 p 7 </F>

<F P=103> HK1206052194 </F>
<F P=104>  Hong Kong HONG KONG STANDARD </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Didi Tatlow] </F>
  [Excerpts] A Foreign Ministry spokesman yesterday 
dismissed as "sheer fabrication" a report that a major reshuffle 
is to take place within the ministry. 
  The report, carried yesterday by the SING TAO DAILY NEWS, 
said that Foreign Minister Qian Qichen was to be replaced by Luo 
Gan, secretary-general of the State Council and Premier Li 
Peng's "right-hand man". [passage omitted] 
  The spokesman declined to comment further on the report, 
which said that the reshuffle was part of a plan by Mr Li to 
strengthen his control over China's foreign affairs. [passage 
omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

