  [Text] Moscow, June 13 (XINHUA) -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin discussed with his U.S. counterpart Bill Clinton today 
through telephone the nuclear problem on the Korean peninsula 
and the ways to settle it through political means. 
  During the conversation, the two presidents discussed a U.N. 
